Qeqertalik Climate

Qeqertalik Climate Summary

Located at an elevation of 9.03 meters (29.63 feet) above sea level, Qeqertalik has a Tundra climate (Classification: ET). The city’s yearly temperature is -5.62ºC (21.88ºF) and it is 4.45% higher than Greenland’s averages. Qeqertalik typically receives about 16.35 millimeters (0.64 inches) of precipitation and has 48.91 rainy days (13.4% of the time) annually.
